Conversion Specification:

%[flag][minimum field width][precision][length modifier][conversion specifier]
%-m.pX

-        left justification
m        minimum field width
p        precision
X        conversion specifier

Precision:

float-point number(%e, %f)    the number of digits printed after the decimal point.
float-point number(%g)        the maximum number of significant digits.
integer(%d)                   the minimum number of digits printed,
                              if necessary extra zero are added to the beginning of the number.
integer(%.0d)                 special case, means no output when number is zero.
string(%s)                    the maximum length of the string displayed.

